    {"intent_id": "proscons_typescript", "query": "what are the pros and cons of TypeScript", "response": "Pros: catch bugs at compile time, better IDE support (autocomplete, refactoring), self-documenting code, easier large-scale maintenance, gradual adoption possible. Cons: compilation step, learning curve (generics, type gymnastics), slower development initially, type definition maintenance, some libraries lack types. Worth it for any project beyond small scripts.", "variant": "list"},
