    {"intent_id": "prod_pomodoro", "query": "what is the Pomodoro technique", "response": "The Pomodoro technique is a time management method: work for 25 minutes (one 'pomodoro'), then take a 5-minute break. After 4 pomodoros, take a 15-30 minute break. Benefits: maintains focus, prevents burnout, makes large tasks manageable. Track completed pomodoros to measure productivity.", "variant": "short"},
